"If the strong king occupies one of the key squares, the pawn promotes. When the pawn is on the 5th rank, its key squares are those three in front ( e6, f6 and g6, marked in the diagram )."

Since the king has reached one of them, White wins:
1. ‚ôîf6! } { [%csl Re6,Rf6,Rg6][%cal Ge6f6] }
